Date: Wed, 5 Jun 2019 18:29:07 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] ASoC: fsl_sai: support shared interrupts

The LS1028A SoC shares interrupts between SAIs.

Signed-off-by: Michael Walle <michael.walle@kontron.com>
---
 sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c b/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
index 44ea7bb5f4c9..36658572f8fe 100644
--- a/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
+++ b/sound/soc/fsl/fsl_sai.c
@@ -853,7 +853,8 @@ static int fsl_sai_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return irq;
 	}
 
-	ret = devm_request_irq(&pdev->dev, irq, fsl_sai_isr, 0, np->name, sai);
+	ret = devm_request_irq(&pdev->dev, irq, fsl_sai_isr, IRQF_SHARED,
+			       np->name, sai);
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(&pdev->dev, "failed to claim irq %u\n", irq);
 		return ret;
